"Yokouchi Y., Nojiri Y., Barrie L.A., Toom-Sauntry D., Fujinuma Y.","Atmospheric methyl iodide: High correlation with surface seawater temperature and its implications on the sea-to-air flux",2001,"Journal of Geophysical Research Atmospheres","106","D12", 2001JD900083,"12661","12668",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0034925063&partnerID=40&md5=52db283977699903216f93da0e3fd2da","Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, Tsukuba, Ibaraki, Japan; Atmospheric Environment Service, Toronto, Ont., Canada; Atmosph. Sci. Global Change Rsrc. E., Richland, WA, United States; Atmosph. Sci. Global Change Rsrc. E., Battelle Boulevard, Richland, WA 99362, United States; Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, 16-2 Onogawa, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0053, Japan; Atmospheric Environment Service, 4905 Dufferin Street, Toronto, Ont. M3H 5T4, Canada","Yokouchi, Y., Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, Tsukuba, Ibaraki, Japan, Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, 16-2 Onogawa, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0053, Japan; Nojiri, Y., Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, Tsukuba, Ibaraki, Japan, Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, 16-2 Onogawa, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0053, Japan; Barrie, L.A., Atmospheric Environment Service, Toronto, Ont., Canada, Atmosph. Sci. Global Change Rsrc. E., Richland, WA, United States, Atmosph. Sci. Global Change Rsrc. E., Battelle Boulevard, Richland, WA 99362, United States; Toom-Sauntry, D., Atmospheric Environment Service, Toronto, Ont., Canada, Atmospheric Environment Service, 4905 Dufferin Street, Toronto, Ont. M3H 5T4, Canada; Fujinuma, Y., Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, Tsukuba, Ibaraki, Japan, Natl. Inst. for Environ. Studies, 16-2 Onogawa, Tsukuba, Ibaraki 305-0053, Japan","Intensive measurements of atmospheric methyl iodide taken at high, middle, and low latitudes over a period of 3 years have provided evidence for its photochemical production in seawater and given new information that sea-to-air transport of CH<inf>3</inf>I is mainly controlled by surface seawater temperature (SST). These findings suggest a highly localized production and distribution of CH<inf>3</inf>I in the surface microlayer. As a result, the oceanic emission of CH<inf>3</inf>I is likely to be larger than previous estimates based on the classical two-layer model. Owing to the SST dependence of atmospheric CH<inf>3</inf>I concentration, its impact on tropospheric or stratospheric ozone depletion would be increased by El Nino or future global warming. Copyright 2001 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"air-sea interaction; iodide; marine atmosphere; sea surface temperature; Pacific Ocean",,,,,,"Bassford, M.R., Nickless, G., Simmonds, P.G., Lewis, A.C., Pilling, M.J., Evans, M.J., The concurrent observation of methyl iodide and dimethyl sulphide in marine air; Implications for sources of atmospheric methyl iodide (1999) Atmos. Environ., 33, pp. 2373-2383; Blake, D.R., Blake, N.J., Smith Jr., T.W., Wingenter, O.W., Rowland, F.S., Nonmethane hydrocarbon and halocarbon distributions during Atlantic Stratocumulus Transition Experiment/Marine Aerosol and Gas Exchange, June 1992 (1996) J. Geophys. Res., 101 (D2), pp. 4501-4514; Carlson, D.J., Surface microlayer phenolic enrichments indicate sea surface slicks (1982) Nature, 296, pp. 426-429; Carpenter, L.J., Sturges, W.T., Penkett, S.A., Liss, P.S., Alicke, B., Hebestreit, K., Platt, U., Short-lived alkyl iodides and bromides at Mace Head, Ireland: Links to biogenic sources and halogen oxide production (1999) J. Geophys. Res., 104 (D1), pp. 1679-1689; Chameides, W.L., Davis, D.D., Iodine: Its possible role in tropospheric photochemistry (1980) J. Geophys. Res., 85 (C12), pp. 7383-7398; Ekdahl, A., Pedersen, M., Abrahamsson, K., A study of the diurnal variation of biogeic volatile halocarbons (1998) Mar. Chem., 63, pp. 1-8; Gershey, R.M., Characterization of seawater organic matter carried by bubble-generated aerosols (1983) Limnol. Oceanogr., 28, pp. 309-319; Gschwend, P.M., MacFarlane, J.K., Newman, K.A., Volatil